@node features "Features"

                               Features

-Simple installation: just run the game and play!

-X_Next is a "Workbench" game, so it is meant to be played on the
 Workbench screen. The game window can be resized up to a maximum
 of 640 x 400 pixels, and the game is redisplayed according to the
 new window size. If the window is too small, it will automatically
 be resized to an adequate displayable size.

-As the game uses as little of the computer's ressources as
 possible, you can run other applications, games, etc. at the same
 time.

-X_Next works on all Amigas with Workbench 1.3 or higher.

@endnode

@node histo "History"

                           Versions History

  What follows are the various updates that were done since the
first version of this game.

V1.0:

-First public release.

V1.1:

-Now all boards are generated when the game is run, instead of one
 board at a time when a new board is being displayed.
-The scoring routine has been revised. Now when a player moves on
 a tile that has a number on it, the player gets that amount of
 points. If a tile has no number on it, one point is added to the
 score.
-The game board ending sequence has been revised.
-The routine that takes the game colours from the Workbench palette
 has been revised. Now, depending on the amount of colours the
 Workbench uses, the game takes its colours from a sample of up to
 256 colours from the Workbench palette. Originally, the game took
 its colours using only the first 16 colours, as it was a bit
 limiting for the game... Big thanks goes to Mikhail Malyshev to
 have brought this to my attention.
-The routine that draws the numbers on the tiles has been revised.
-Now the player can quit the game by pressing on the 'Esc' key.
-The pull-down menu has been removed.
-The routine that checks if the game window is too small has been
 revised.
-The 'About' routine has been revised.
-Some unneeded program code have been removed.
-Various additional changes have been made.

@endnode

@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'X_Next' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  The goal is to remove all the tiles that are shown on a game
board. You can move on any tile, by clicking on them, except those
that are located next to your current position (your position is
indicated by an 'X' shaped object).

  As you move from one tile to another, the previous tile you were
on will disappear (unless it has a number on it), just watch out
that there are at least one tile that is not immediately next to
your position because otherwise, the game will be over.

  Some tiles have numbers from 2 to 5 on them; every time you leave
such a tile, its number will decrease by one unit, so you can go to
these tiles that number of times before they disappear. You get
points according to the number that is shown on the tile you move
to. If the tile has no number you get one point.

  Have fun!

  To quit the game, click on the game window's close button or
press the 'Esc' key.

@endnode

